We'd like you to meet <b>KJ</b>, our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>KJ moved to Millsberry on January 5th, 2007. He's been enjoying his <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/home/?user=sandersjck"><a href='/home/?user=sandersjck'>84170-B Broken Tree Bend</a></a> residence for over a year now, and it's only gotten better with time. <br><br>KJ loves spending time at the Millsberry arcade, but he also has his own person arcade right in his house. Not only is the comfort and convenience a plus, but KJ's arcade also boasts a mix of games unique to his home. Where else can you enjoy a lively game of indoor badminton?<br><br>Head out to KJ's backyard and you'll find his collection of surfboards. He's got a hang loose fish, aloha fun board, wave pattern short board, and a reach-the-sky long board. If your appetite happens to grow, you can always serve up some burgers and hotdogs on KJ's grill. His backyard is the perfect recipe for a summer time hangout. <br><br>During the other three seasons of the year, you can always enjoy the hot tub KJ installed in his living room. It's positioned just well enough to get a great view of his flat screen TV. If you're watching something exciting, try to refrain from splashing. <br><br>KJ describes himself as being very sporty. This would explain his Home Run derby and Hockey trophies. KJ is also environmentally conscious. He participated in the Peabody Park clean up. When he's not making our world a better place, he's probably saving the galaxy, considering he also mastered Galactic Defender.<br><br>When you happen to see KJ, congratulate him and thank him for being such an outstanding citizen.<br></div>
